commentPostTextItems.html: Tahst the end of the match here at Karachi
Pakistan go 1-0 up in the most authoritative way
They put up a massive total of 275 for 6 in their 50 overs
Youhana was the chief architect of that 275 - Younis Khan supported him well and Razzaq fires at the end
Back when they came with the ball, the Ws, Waqar and Wasim picked up one wicket each and set the ball rolling
Shoaib Akhtar who came in to bowl after that pwas as usual terribly quick and picked up 6 wickets in super style
The Samsung award for maximum sixes will be shared by Astle and Razzaq for hitting 2 sixes each
Yousuf Youhana gets the award for hitting the maximum boundaries
The fastest fifty award goes to Younis Khan for hitting it in 69 balls
Shoaib Akhtar is Man of the Match for his fiery 6 for 17
Get back to us on Wednesday, 24 April, 2002 for the 2nd ODI between these 2 teams
It starts at 1530 hrs. PST, (0930 hrs. GMT)
Until then, its bye bye from all of us here at CricInfo.com
